                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> And not to be left out on the goodness...<br /><br /><a href="http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm55.showMessage?topicID=27.topic" target="_blank">http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm55.showMessage?topicID=27.topic</a><br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">The Raiding Bard. V 1.03 <br /><br />First of all this is more of a set of guidelines then rules. If your expecting cold hard facts you won't get them. Im writing this so bards new to raiding can get a sense for what they should be doing.<br /><br />On any given raid there are several tasks that can or should be done by a bard. Its important to remember that most fights in PoP are unique so deciding what is most important in any given situation is what seperates you from the herd. You should be able to handle a few of these at a time at least. Also in situations where there are multipul bards it will help if you discuss with them beforehand who is going to be doing what. If you find yourself the only bard on a raid its upto you to cover as many of these as possible. In no particular order the main bard duties are as follows.<br /><br />-Marr or manabitch duty. Self explainitory, when your on this duty its your job to keep Chorus of Marr(64), Ancient: Lcea's Lament(60), or Chorus of Replenishment(5 up at all times.<br /><br />-Resist duty. This can be more complicated then Marr but its still simple. Know what resist you should be playing for any given mob before engaging and play Purifying Chorus(56) for PR/DR/MR or Elemental Chorus(54) for FR/CR/MR. In some cases you might not know which resist you will need to have up beforehand if thats the case have both ready. You can't twist these songs but once you figure out which is needed more keep that up.<br /><br />-Resist debuff duty. This one is pretty easy as well. Set up a hotkey &lt;preferably in a debuffer channel&gt; and play Harmony of Sound(65) or Occlusion of Sound(55) on all incoming mobs. Because these songs are unresistable you can tap your hotkey as soon as you start singing the song. This will let casters start casting whatever they are going to at the mob since its most likely got a longer casting time then 3 seconds. You will need a drum or epic in hand to do this. Also to lower specific resists you can twist in your chants.<br /><br />-Mezzing adds. This one is a little more dangerous. Load up your highest mez song: Lullaby of Morell(65), Dreams of Terris(64), Dreams of Thule(62), Dreams of Ayonae(5 , or Song of Twilight(53). Once you have your mez loaded keep on the lookout for adds and mez any you see. You may also want to load your resist debuff and tag a mob with that before mezzing if you are getting too many resists. If your in an area where mobs are low enough you can use Ancient: Lullaby of Shadow(60) as this song has a much better chance of not getting resisted. This duty be left to enchanters most of the time if they are present.<br /><br />-Maintank or damageshield duty. When your on this its your job to crank out as much damageshield as possible. The best twist for DSing is Warsong of Zek(62), Amplification(30), and of Psalm of Veeshan(63). If your maintank is recieving Divine Intervention or a similar from clerics you can add in Solon's Charismatic Concord after amplification to improve their chances of it going off and saving their life.<br /><br />-Cleric babysitting duty. In situations where your raid force is split up you may get to sit with the clerics. You will want to crank out as much mana as possible to support their constant complete heal casting. If your clerics are not in range of another bard playing Chorus of Marr twist Chorus of Marr, Amplification, two ticks of Cassindra's Chorus of Clarity(32), then Chorus again, two more ticks of Cassindra's and repeat from the begining. If your near another bard just twist Amplification then Cassindra's until Amp wears off and repeat.<br /><br />-DPS duty. When the other duties are all covered you can always grab up a few nukers or DPS melee and twist Warsong of Zek, and Rizlona's Call of Flame. When Im doing this I usually pick up Marr duty and play Psalm of Veeshan to help keep my group alive. If Marr duty is covered you can twist Warsong of Zek, Amplification, Rizlona's Call of Flame, and Psalm of Veeshan<br /><br />-Group resists. When your facing a mob with a difficult to resist ae you may choose to twist amplification and Psalm of Veeshan with whichever resist chorus you have up so that you can live longer to keep playing resists.<br /><br />-Mana Seive duty. This one doesn't come up often in PoP but there are some situations where you may find that its easier to a mob who has been drained of their mana supply. The best method for this is to equip your best brass mod and use Ervaj's Lost Composition(60). Depending on the mana pool of the mob they should be drained fairly quickly.<br /><br />-Pulling. Pulling is one of the more advanced tasks you may get stuck with and only the most skilled should attempt this as messing up can get you and the raid killed. First of all know where the mobs are in the area your pulling, you can use Lyssa's Solidarity of Vision(34) to peek around corners and such using targeted mobs are waypoints for your camera. Once you are comfortable with pathing and agro range your ready to pull. Get a charisma buff from a shaman or enchanter and load up Silent Song of Quellious(61), Harmony of Sound or Occulusion of Sound, and Requiem of Time(64). If you don't have Requiem load up your favorite long range no damage song. Now its time to pull, move forward in the direction your raid is headed and peak slowly around corners. You can usually use corners to block mobs from agroing on you while you target and lull them, lull all the mobs in the area around your target and then with your target selected turn around and HoS or OoS them once they are agroed start running back to your camp and en route tag them with Requiem of Time. At your camp stop next to the Main tank/assist and let them get agro. Congratulations you just delivered a preslowed mob to your raid. Rinse and repeat.<br /><br />Dangers. While raiding part of your job is to stay alive so you can help keep others alive. Some things that will help you stay alive are Kazumi's Note of Preservation and the Fading Memories AA. Some of the main dangers you will face are listed below, they are all avoidable but can happen on accident sometimes so its good to know how to save yourself.<br /><br />-A trick that has saved many a bards life is to have Kazumi's Note of Preservation(60) memmed. If a raid is wiping sing Kazumi's and sit down and start camping immiediatly, count 3 seconds after camp timer says 15 and tap a premade /disc deftdance key. This will give you time to camp out safely. If your raid has a channel set up you should og onto another character and join the channel to see when it will be safe to log back in.<br /><br />-If you have an ae song up when mobs are being pulled you can catch agro if it pulses before a tank taunts. You can probably handle getting beat on for a few second but its healthier to tap fading memories, By the time the mob is in the camp and hitting you someone else should have some agro so its easy enough to lose it. <br /><br />-If you have an ae song up before fighting a boss mob you may get on the rampage list. If you get on the rampage list back out of melee range stop all your songs and tap Fading Memories once. Hopefully some other poor bastard will take your place on the rampage list. When you need to have songs up before engaging a mob you can avoid rampage most of the time by twisting your songs directly before the mob is pulled/agroed/spawned letting them stop for a few seconds while the maintank and hopefully the rampage tank build up their agro. Waiting till the mob is at 98-97% is sufficient most of the time.<br /><br />-If your resists aren't high enough on a mob with a damaging ae effect you may get low hitpoint agro. If your getting low hitpoints moves the mob around you may get those whole raid killed. Very bad idea, know who will be free to heal you during the fight and get your resists up.<br /><br />Unfortunatly everyone dies sometimes make sure you have some premade song lists for every situation.<br /><br />The important thing to remember is that while this list may help you in some situations it is not the end all be all for raiding. Learn your songs and get creative. If you have an additions or corrections please send them to me at <a href="mailto:Satan_burninhell@hotmail.com">Satan_burninhell@hotmail.com</a> <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                </td>
